    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>An optical effect manifested as a series of alternating light and dark colored bands; generally caused when one piece of glass with a curved surface rests on another with a flat surface, resulting in an interference of light waves. Named for the English physicist Sir Isaac Newton who first investigated their properties.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
